N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4231.12 - Objection to matters occurring in race

State Regulations

An objection to a horse on the ground of his not having
run the proper course or of the race having been run on a wrong course or of
any other matter occurring in the race must be made before the numbers of the
horses placed in the race are confirmed officially. Notes
